dhood we did, yes, until we got too old to have a nurse and then - but I can't remember quite because as I say our age - our ages range from - now wait a minute, what difference is there between my - elder sister? Oh - yes - she's four - four years older 
t
han I am and the youngest is ten years younger so there must have been fourteen or fifteen, our ages range from about fourteen to fifteen to about a - a year you see, under a the year or so, we had it up to that and then - when we got I suppose when we al
l got a bit older we did away with a nanny, you see, because it wasn't necessary. Got beyond the nursery age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Was there one that you particularly remember who stayed longer than the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No, I should think dear Edith who - whose name I remembe
r must have been - I should think she was probably the last one. And she was - she was very nice, I remember her vaguely. Not what she looked like in the least but I remember she was very sweet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 They looked after you?
