So your parents really didn't have children about that they felt would be bad company for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh no, I'm sure they wouldn't have done, no, no, I'm sure they wouldn't, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Those sort of children weren't near at hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh no, oh no, they wouldn't have been round us, no. And at school we wouldn't really have had that type I don't think we should have been attracted to them - actually, I don't mean that in a snobbish but I mean - like - like to like, yes, quite.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Do you remember if your mother ever being ill or when she was confined with your younger sisters, how she managed, did she have anybody come in and help her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh yes, I think she did and of course - I think - I think were all born at home, I don't think there was any question of any - mother going to hospital at all, I don't remember that, no. But - when the last -
 my youngest sister was born - I I knew - I was just ten so I suppose in those days children weren't told what they are told now and so we didn't know very much at that age then and I was sent - to live - to stay with some friends - in - not very far away
, until it was all over. But I do - I do remember that one, but that was my youngest sister, but then as I say she was ten years younger than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Was it a surprise when you came back, did you know beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Well I - I think we had an idea that 
we - but - it wasn't, no, it wasn't spelt out you see, not like it is these days, all children know long before you're going to have - oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Relatives living nearby, your mother's parents had died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 My father's parents had died, that's right. M
y mother's parents visited, but they both came from Surbiton, both families. We never knew my father's family because - they - they died before we were ever born.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 And you said you had an aunt who lived in Clapham, an elderly aunt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 That's right, 
and I remember I going in the horse tram buses, yes. On Clapham Hill, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Any other relations who you regularly saw, who sort of featured in your life?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Well - we had a great-uncle who lived at Bournemouth. And - we often used to go and - you kn
ow, go and stay down there with him for holidays and that - that sort of - that sort of thing. But I think our main relatives were nearly all in Surbiton, because both sides of the family came from Surbiton you see. Although we had lots of friends all ove
r the place, but - that particular uncle was my - father's - no he's not a great-uncle, that's right, he was my father's uncle, and he had a lovely house, he had plenty of money, a lovely house and we used to go and - do you know Bournemouth at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 I've just been there once.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh only once, well, there was a stream that used to run through the gardens, I always remember that - everybody paddled there, all children paddled there, sail your boats and that sort of thing. Oh used to go often to stay wi
th him, yes. Very often to stay with him.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What about cousins, did you have cousins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Now we had - wait a minute - yes, we've got quite a - well, we had some cousins on my mother's side - which - which we were much fonder of and saw a great deal 
more of than my father's side. We weren't violently keen on any of those, we saw them occasionally, but - I don't - I can't remember making any special efforts to see them unless they - but these - but my mother's side, yes, we had lots of very nice cousi
ns, and we saw each other a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
I often think that's something that your generation sort of had extra kind of support from, those cousins and things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Now people don't seem to bother much with cousins,
