Well - I think they mostly came - in the afternoon, perhaps stayed and had a cup of tea because that was the easiest thing to get - to get, when they hadn't been prepared for it you know and if 
you want to have anybody really for a meal one wants to know - roughly when they mean to be there otherwise you might get short rations or something. No, I think people enjoyed just a short social call in the afternoon and have tea, the only - the only th
ing then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Would they sort of walk round?
