Oh they were - they were so nice, the shopkeepers, I - oh yes, now that's one of the things I do think we miss terribly. I mean - they had - we didn't have the - what do you call the - amount of g
oods for the simple reason they didn't have the capital to buy them and secondly because they hadn't the space for them. But the attention - that - I mean - mother was loved by all shopkeepers, I know, rushed to serve her as soon as she got inside the sho
p, and they would all of them - you know, send their goods to her, send them home so she - you know, she didn't have to lift very \{BLANK\}
 except big places like Barkers or Harrods or Selfridges, somewhere like that. But - that - that was fun, we used to lov
e - we loved to go to the shops because they all knew us you see, in - they knew mother and they knew we were mother's children. Quite often we would get a few sweets. Oh no, I'm - that - that I'm very sorry we've lost because - there was something quite 
o
n their own. They really did take pride in serving their customers. And - and see - seeing that they got what they wanted, well they had to for a living now because you see they would have been - I mean look - look at some of them now - with the big super
markets, they just - they've gone under, but there's no - alternative.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What social class would you have put them in at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh well, now, some of them were quite superior actually. I - I - I wouldn't have put them all as - as - now, but I 
just - I don't mean to degrade the poor charwomen by any manner or means, but I would say they came between the two. They were a little superior, the average one, to a charwomen, and not quite what we would call our best middle class. But - I - I - that w
ouldn't worry me at all. Not in the least.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Did any of their children go to the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
I - don't - not when I was there I don't think, I mean, later on - might have been when I'd left and things changed a bit, but I don't - I don't think so, I don't remember them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What about clergy in Wimbledon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh we, had - we had - yes, several - oh - yes - well - there were two of them, they were very very charming in our church, very sweet indeed, they were awfully nice, and - they used to come to Sunday supper with us occasionally \{BLANK\}
 or something like that. And - I - they were - yes, they were very - and they used to call a lot and - you know, they knew us very well, all of them I mean - you know, because - I said - I think I said - told you my
 father was a sidesman, and - we all went as children we trouped into a pew, the children, and they - you know, it was always sort of known as the Hewitt pew, because we took up a whole pew with six of us you see. That's right, that's - oh that is it - oh
 yes, you were going to see that weren't you. It was really delightful wasn't it. I think the young boy was extremely good. Very good, because it's a difficult part to play really. Oh I enjoyed it tremendously, I could see it again really, quite easily.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember any teachers, did your parents know any teachers socially?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
I think occasionally we had - oh yes, I think some - one or two of my - mistresses that I - that taught me for quite a while and - whom I liked very much came quite often to have tea. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Which social class would you have put them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh well I would have put them in ours definitely. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember any non-conformist people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 You didn't know them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No. I mean - I - no, I didn't. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What sort of people would you say went to church and to chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
I wondered if you were conscious of them being different classes or different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No - - no, not really. Not classes in the stri
ct sense of social classes, but perhaps - the only way perhaps I could describe it is frightfully - bigoted a bit. You know - I think - yes, just a little bit, you know, rather - yes, narrow, that's a better word, narrow is a better word. Yes, 'cos they -
 
they - you - you see, some people as you know now like a sort of - a very high church, other like - others like a medium and I always think the non-conformists are rather on the side when they - I don't know, very - rather dreary about it all. Or were the
n, as I say, I don't know what they are now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Within the middle class were you aware of different standards of living within that class when you were as child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Well, only insofar as - I think - not for any - not in any other way except that if som
ebody - certain people might have a good deal more money than others, and - in which case of course they had something more - opportunity of entertaining. But I wouldn't say so otherwise, no, it's a question of that as to whether they might be able to - e
ntertain more, because they had the money to entertain with.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember any difference in dress or did the money not affect that?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
No, I don't think that was affected, it was - no, it was just that they were able to - they were just able to entertain more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Were you aware of a distinction between craftsmen and labourers, skilled men who'd served their time,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What, do you mean personally or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Were you sort of aware that in the working class that some were much better off than others because they were artisans, had a skill and a trade?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Yes. Oh I see. Yes. Oh you mean like for instance watch jewelers and watchmakers and people like that. Carpenters and joiners. No, I think they - no, I - I think - no, I think they were all muc
h of the same - in their own class you know and they were very - very good and skilled at their craft. I wish some of them were more skilled nowadays, had a care and - and had a little more desire, but they don't you know, couldn't care less these days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 So really you don't remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No, I can't remember, no, not definitely, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 From your background you wouldn't have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No, probably not, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
People say there were very great distinctions within the sort of working class themselves between those who had a skill, a trade, and those who didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh that I - I really don't know, I couldn't say - no, I don't - it - it probably was so but I just didn't - don't remember it actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember people being described as a real g
entleman and a real lady when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 What was the reason when they said that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Well - I think - well particularly I should say that they had - they had - knew how to - carry themselves and - and how to speak, 
and they were - well the word says gentle men and gentle women, you know, they knew how - things should be done. I suppose that's how the name - the name of the - expression originated. I imagine so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging t
o a certain particular social class or don't you think she thought about that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
No, no, I don't think so, she was far too - no, I don't think so, she wasn't class conscious my - no, not to my knowledge at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 And your father, do you know if he was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
No, I don't think so. No, they - no, no, they don't - what I can remember I wouldn't call them either class - either of them class conscious.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
You weren't brought up as some people are with a very strong consciousness of belonging to a particular class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh no, no, not at all, oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh you mean, to be friendly with one class or to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 To leave your class and go up or to go }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid13897837\charrsid9008311 downwards}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh I see. No, I don't think so. No. Not - I can't remember that, no, not to my knowledge, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember seeing a policeman round where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Were there policemen on the beat in that area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Oh yes, quite often. Oh yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
How do you think he treated the people or weren't you aware of that when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
No, I don't think I was aware of it particularly because in those days they didn't have these violent mobs to control and
 they were really very - you know, very helpful and nice. I get so cross sometimes when the people I know, they - they do get brutal with some of the police, but good gracious me, when you think of what they have to put up with. Oh goodness me they do, an
d it's always - and it's always the poor policemen they say is brutal, what about the people who start the rummage. \{BLANK\} I mean, they have an awful lot to put up with, policeman I think, I think
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Do you remember if your mother ever said, I'll call a 
policeman if you are naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Oh she might have said it in fun but I don't think she really meant it, no, no. She might have said it in fun because that is the sort of - Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Did you own your home or was it rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 No, it was owned.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
You were telling me before how your parents didn't have a lot of money because of your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Well, no, because I mean a professional artist was - a professional man with six children to educate and clothe and feed you and - unless you're very 
very exceptional. Oh we got - we got by because my mother's parents were well of and - and I think my father's parents had been very well off, we didn't get - we did get by.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Did they help your parents financially do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 I should think - I
 - well - I - obviously - not my - father's parents because of course by the time he was - he was married and had the family they were no longer here, I mean he - what they left for him he had obviously, but my mother - I'm sure my mother and father - mot
her's parents, particularly because they were - he was - very well off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid4021532 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 
Do you ever remember feeling at any time in your childhood that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid10557675 HS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid11872452\charrsid9008311 Yes - not while he was - not while he was alive. When he died 
mother certainly had a struggle. Definitely, yes.
